- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on analyzing the social media activities of a protest movement against refugee housing in Germany. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) is also likely as the paper investigates the patterns of communication and interaction among users of far-right social media sites and pages. 
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy) is a possible category as the paper may touch upon issues related to online privacy and security in the context of social media activities. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is another possible category as the paper may use natural language processing techniques to analyze the content of social media posts and comments. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a less likely category, but the paper may touch upon issues related to online security and privacy in the context of social media activities.
